Accounting is the process of recording financial transactions. Our Accounting major prepares you for careers in auditing, tax, and finance.
The Agricultural major focuses on modern farming, food production, and sustainability. Learn about crop science, agribusiness, and more.
Architecture is the art and science of designing buildings. Our Architecture major covers design, engineering, and urban planning.
Artificial Intelligence (AI) is about creating smart machines. Our AI major covers machine learning, robotics, and data science.
The Business major teaches management, marketing, finance, and entrepreneurship skills for a variety of industries.
Chemical Engineering combines chemistry, physics, and math to solve problems involving chemicals, fuel, drugs, and food.
Computer Science is the study of computers and computational systems. Learn programming, algorithms, and software development.
Cyber Security focuses on protecting systems and data from cyber threats. Learn about network security, cryptography, and ethical hacking.
Data Science is about extracting insights from data. Our major covers statistics, machine learning, and big data technologies.
Engineering applies science and math to solve real-world problems. We offer various engineering majors including mechanical, electrical, and civil.
Finance is the study of money management. Our major covers investment, banking, and financial analysis.
Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) focuses on designing user-friendly interfaces and improving user experience with technology.
Human Resources (HR) is about managing people in organizations. Learn about recruitment, training, and employee relations.
Information Systems combines business and technology to manage information. Learn about databases, systems analysis, and IT management.
The Internet of Things (IoT) connects devices to the internet. Our IoT major covers sensors, networks, and smart systems.
